But whatever, I get it, bitch did a stitch or two in New Orleans or Atlantic City or who knows where, Pittsburgh. Is Boston on the Eastern Seaboard ?">xi</a></sup> A wealthy white fence and gambler had tricked with her out there, and it had gotten so good to him that he crossed<sup><a href="#footnote_11_97312" id="identifier_11_97312" class="footnote-link footnote-identifier-link" title="Since they're using `trick` to describe punting they're stuck using `crossing` to describe... tricking. If robohitler re-introduces crucifiction for being annoying / the wrong color / whatever, they're probably going to call it... hm. Punting. Why not.
